    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for cockpit-image-builder.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 10.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The image-builder-frontend generates custom images suitable for deploying systems or uploading to the cloud. It integrates into Cockpit as a frontend for osbuild.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* lodash: prototype pollution in _.unset and _.omit functions (CVE-2025-13465)\n\n* lodash: lodash: Arbitrary code execution via untrusted input in template imports (CVE-2026-4800)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
